addChild(address).details: Functionality for adding a child to the parental wallet

params.child: : Address of the user being added to the parental wallet as a child Notice: A user with parent role can't be assigned a child role.

addParent(address).details: Functionality for adding another parent to the parental wallet

params.parent: Address of the user being added to the parental wallet as an parent Notice: A user with child role cannot be added as a parent.

params._txIndex: Index of the transaction to be confirmed

depositEth().details: Functionality for depositing funds into the Parental wallet. Anyone can add deposit funds to this parental wallet.

params._txIndex: Index of the transaction to be executed

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

removeChild(address).details: Functionality for removing a child from the parental wallet.

params.child: : Address of the user being removed from the parental wallet as a child

removeParent(address).details: Functionality for removing a parent from the parental wallet

params.parent: : Address of the user being removed from the parental wallet as an parent Notice: First parent cannot be removed.

removeTx(uint256).details: Functionality for removing a transaction from the logs

params._txIndex: Index of the transaction to be removed

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

params._txIndex: : Index of the transaction confirmation to be revoked

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

params._value: Amount to be sent Notice: Anyone with child and parent role can submit a transaction.

withdrawEth(uint256).details: Functionality for withdrawing funds from the Parental wallet.

params._amount: : amount to be withdrawn. Requirnments: Only the parent can withdraw funds.
